 ## Risks / things to watch
 
-- **Stale references in live text.** A grep for `run_experiment` after the change must turn up zero hits in `reference/`, `AGENTS.md`, and `docs/roadmap.md`. Hits in `docs/plans/eden-phase-8c-cutover.md` (this plan, by design) and in `docs/plans/eden-phase-{0,1-â€¦,7a,7b,8a,8b}-*.md` plus `docs/plans/review/**` (frozen historical artifacts) are expected and excluded from the check.
+- **Stale references in live source.** A grep for `run_experiment` in `reference/packages/` and `reference/services/` after the change must turn up zero hits â€” every live-source mention of the deleted symbol must either be removed or rephrased to reference `run_orchestrator_iteration`. Narrative-changelog mentions in `AGENTS.md` and `docs/roadmap.md` are deliberately preserved and reworded to past tense ("was deleted in Phase 8c") so a contributor searching for the deleted symbol still finds the explanation.
 - **Test-file deletion vs. coverage gap.** The risk is that `test_end_to_end.py` exercised an invariant the e2e + orchestrator-iteration tests do not. Walked through above; the only such case is the malformed-success routing test, which is rewritten rather than dropped.
 - **Worker hosts' scripted `plan_fn` profiles.** The plan-task-list generation in `_common/scripted.py` was originally validated by `test_end_to_end.py`'s plan_fn shape. The e2e test exercises the same shape end-to-end (it asserts `parent_commits == [base_sha]` and verifies three trials), so the coverage transfers cleanly.
 - **CI cache.** Removing a test file does not invalidate any cache key; pyright and ruff will rerun against the smaller tree without issue.
